This paper involves the application of deep reinforcement learning to solve a complex control problem in a video game, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also proposes several novel strategies for training the actor-critic network, which involves techniques from machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). The problem of controlling actions in a game also has connections to game theory (cs.GT) and control systems (cs.SY).
